Resolving (No action, Obsolete)

(But it should have been, at some point.)

It appears that there are still open seats for the course but these seats pertain to graduate students. If graduate students do not take those open seats can undergraduate students who are currently in the waitlist be enrolled and take their spot?

Some discussion sections appears to be close for both grad/undergrad, but some are still open for undergrad (as is my case with my discussion). 

[I was about 70 in the waitlist when there were around 130+ seats open but due to a conflict, switching the discussion and dropping the class lowered me in the class waitlist... I am undeclared and wasn't able to enroll in any upper division cs class]
